review_blob: Nice and spicy, very tasty.

Wow!  A friend of mine mentioned this to me and I drove to Rhode Island simply to get a bottle.  The flavor of the malts is amazing, though I found the alcohol to be a little too apparent, more like a wine.  It leaves a little too sweet of a taste on the palate, which is why I didnt give it a 20.
Its drinkable, but really not very good.

Haha, I think its amazing that there are enough 5.0 rankings featuring a caption long live the beast to even keep this things rating above 1.0.  This stuff is terrible, though I will confess to drinking it in large quantities at least once.  Has to be made from unfiltered water from the ganges river.  This beer will kick you in the stomach and then bash you in the ribs while youre already defenseless.
Oh yeah!  Big burnt chocolatey flavor.  One of my absolute favorites.
Bad, just bad.  Id rather have a beast.  At least beast doesnt try to be something its not.
Very poor german pils.  Its drinkable when ice-cold, but toward the end of the glass its damn near foul.
Probably the best of the german pils that is exported to the States.  Ill take this over Becks any day.

This is by far the most popular beer in the area that I studied (frankfurt area) and it is not good.  Few beers in Germany are distributed nationally and thus you get some fairly poor local brews like this one.  If you want great german beer, then for gods sake, go to Munich.
Not spectacular, though quite drinkable.
The first time I had this beer was from draft in Belgium and I enjoyed it thoroughly.  It is definitely not as good out of the bottle, too sweet with too many fruit notes and not well balanced.
Excellent sipping beer.
This is not a good beer.  If you want to drink a fruit beer, stick with the belgian stuff and dont waste your money on this.
I find sam adams to be rather inconsistent.  When I get a good bottle it is quite drinkable, but can also be rather poor.
Stone is definitely one of my favorite american breweries.  Great flavorful summer ale.
Excellent!  Robust flavor with a nice dry hopiness.  I dare say a 6.5 ABV may be an underestimate.
This is a fairly decent brew.  Nice coffee flavor, but a little too subtle for a stout.  A little thin too.
Not that good.  The finish had a citrusy bite that really wasnt very pleasant at all.
Whatever that guy on the label is, he definitely has a right to be arrogant about this beer.  Complex malts with a hint of spice and a very bitter hop finish, outstanding.
Fairly overrated, too sweet and not very well balanced.
Perhaps from the tap is is a lot better but from the bottle this is THE most overrated beer in the world.  Pours no head, too thin bodied for a brown and where is the flavor?
What can you really say?
Not a bad porter, though it pours very little head and malts lack character
Definitely one of the best IPAs Ive ever had.
This is a truly fantastic IPA for those who love a strong, lasting hop presence, and at nearly 7% ABV it doesnt lose any drinkability.
